						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the central shrine in the Bṛihadīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Mallikārjuna Śaka [13]74: 1452-53 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of the date of the record except for the Śaka and cyclic years, are lost as it is damaged.</p>						

						<p>This highly damaged record seems to register a grant of land as <hi rend="italic">māṉṉiyam.</hi> It refers to one Kachchirāyaṉ and the village Vaḻudilampaṭṭu. All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
